info.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 26 at 3:56AM PST until February 26 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch. * WHERE...Lowlands of Thurston, western Lewis, and far southeast Mason Counties, including Harstine Island, Olympia, Centralia, and Toledo and Far southwest Mason County and the interior lowlands of Grays Harbor County, including Matlock, McCleary, and Montesano. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning. * IMPACTS...Plan on very difficult travel. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Local total accumulations up to 6 inches over higher terrain near the mountains.
info.instruction: Slow down and use caution while traveling. For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
